# Account & Billing Page Implementation

## Overview

Created a modern SaaS account management page at `/account` displaying user profile, subscription tier, and credit usage with interactive UI components.

---

## Page Features

### 1. Profile & Security Card

**Purpose:** Display user identity and security settings

**Components:**
- **Avatar**: Colorful gradient circle with user initials (first 2 letters of email)
- **Email Address**: Read-only input showing user's email
- **User ID**: Copyable UUID with copy button
- **Sign Out**: Red-themed button using existing [signOut](file:///g:/Prompt%20Guard/app/login/actions.ts#107-113) action

**Design:**
```tsx
<div className="w-24 h-24 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-500 via-purple-500 to-pink-500">
  <span className="text-3xl font-bold">{initials}</span>
</div>
```

---

### 2. Subscription & Usage Card

**Purpose:** Show tier, credit balance, and upgrade options

**Key Elements:**

#### Tier Badge
- **Free**: Cyan badge with Sparkles icon
- **Pro**: Gold gradient badge with Crown icon

```tsx
{tier === 'pro' ? (
  <Badge className="bg-gradient-to-r from-yellow-500 to-orange-500">
    <Crown /> Pro Plan
  </Badge>
) : (
  <Badge className="border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-500/10">
    <Sparkles /> Free Plan
  </Badge>
)}
```

#### Credit Balance Display
- Large gradient typography (5xl font)
- Shows current credits / total limit
- Visual progress bar
- Percentage remaining indicator

```tsx
<span className="text-5xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-400 to-purple-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
  {credits.toLocaleString()}
</span>
```

#### Progress Bar
- Custom Progress component with gradient fill
- Calculates usage: [(credits / creditLimit) * 100](file:///g:/Prompt%20Guard/app/login/actions.ts#7-41)
- Color-coded (cyan to purple gradient)
- Shows percentage and tier limits

#### Action Buttons
- **Upgrade to Pro**: (Free users only) Gradient button
- **View Billing History**: Outline button (placeholder)

#### Pro Benefits (Free users)
- 100,000 credits vs 1,000
- 100 test cases vs 5
- Priority support
- Advanced analytics

---

## Files Created/Modified

### New Files

#### [app/account/page.tsx](file:///g:/Prompt%20Guard/app/account/page.tsx)
```typescript
// Server-side data fetching
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
const { data: profile } = await supabase
  .from('profiles')
  .select('*')
  .eq('id', user.id)
  .single()

// Calculate limits
const creditLimit = tier === 'pro' ? 100000 : 1000
const usagePercentage = (credits / creditLimit) * 100
```

**Features:**
- Redirects to `/login` if not authenticated
- Fetches user + profile data server-side
- Responsive 2-column grid (stacks on mobile)
- Dark theme (`bg-[#050505]`)
- Uses Shadcn UI components

#### [components/ui/progress.tsx](file:///g:/Prompt%20Guard/components/ui/progress.tsx)
```typescript
// Radix UI Progress component
<ProgressPrimitive.Indicator
  className="bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-500 to-purple-500"
  style={{ transform: `translateX(-${100 - (value || 0)}%)` }}
/>
```

### Modified Files

#### [components/navbar.tsx](file:///g:/Prompt%20Guard/components/navbar.tsx)
Added "Account" link next to credits badge:
```tsx
<Link href="/account" className="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-white">
  Account
</Link>
```

