## UI Layout

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Account & Billing                                  │
│  Manage your profile, subscription, and usage       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌──────────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐
│ Personal Information     │  │ Plan & Credits       │
│                          │  │                      │
│       [Avatar AB]        │  │ ✨ Free Plan         │
│                          │  │                      │
│ Email: user@example.com  │  │ 450 / 1,000         │
│ User ID: uuid... [Copy]  │  │ ████░░░░  45%       │
│                          │  │                      │
│ [Sign Out]               │  │ [Upgrade to Pro]    │
└──────────────────────────┘  └──────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Usage Guidelines                                    │
│ • Credits consumed per test run (1 token = 1 credit)│
│ • Free: 1,000 credits, 5 test cases                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Responsive Design

**Desktop (lg+):**
- 2-column grid
- Cards side-by-side
- Full email visible

**Mobile:**
- Single column stack
- Email hidden on small screens
- Maintains all functionality

---

## Components Used

| Component | Source | Purpose |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| `Card` | Shadcn UI | Container cards |
| `Button` | Shadcn UI | Actions (sign out, upgrade) |
| `Input` | Shadcn UI | Email/ID display |
| `Badge` | Shadcn UI | Tier indicator |
| `Progress` | Custom | Credit usage bar |
| Icons | Lucide React | Visual elements |

---

## Navigation

**Access Points:**
1. Click "Account" link in navbar (next to credits badge)
2. Direct URL: `/account`

**Navbar Position:**
```
[Logo] ... [💳 Credits] [Account] [Email] [Sign Out]
```

---

## Key Calculations

```typescript
// Credit limits by tier
const creditLimit = tier === 'pro' ? 100000 : 1000

// Usage percentage
const usagePercentage = (credits / creditLimit) * 100

// User initials for avatar
const initials = email.slice(0, 2).toUpperCase()
```

